thread.title: $A lower ahead of RBA minutes

title: $A lower ahead of RBA minutes
text:
Mon, Aug 17, 2015, 1:08 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 2 hrs 52 mins $A lower ahead of RBA minutes AAP â€“ 43 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is a touch lower, as the currency stabilises following last week's volatility, sparked by the large devaluation in the Chinese yuan. 
At 1200 AEST on Monday, the currency was trading at 73.72 US cents, down from 73.87 cents on Friday. 
With very little economic news out on Monday, trade has been quiet, and investors are waiting for the release of the Reserve Bank of Australia board meeting minutes on Tuesday and the US Federal Reserve July policy meeting minutes, due early on Thursday morning, Sydney time. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 73.72 US cents, from 73.87 cents on Friday 
* 91.70 Japanese yen, from 91.83 yen 
* 66.44 euro cents, from 66.17 euro cents 
* 112.70 New Zealand cents, from 112.83 NZ cents 
* 47.11 British pence, from 47.32 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.946%, from 1.941% on Friday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 2.858%, from 2.868% 
Sydney Futures Exchange prices: 
* The September 2015 10-year bond futures contract was trading at 97.190 (implying a yield of 2.810 per cent), up from 97.185 (2.815 per cent) on Friday. 
* The September 2015 three-year bond futures contract was at 98.020 (1.180 per cent), down from 98.030 (1.970 per cent). 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
